President Obama has declared a major disaster in Maryland and authorized federal aid to support the recovery efforts from the remnants of Tropical Storm Lee. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) has appointed Regis Leo Phelan as the Federal Coordinating Officer for the recovery operations. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA news desk.